                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5016b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-08T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2759. In reply to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CGEB1">Clemenceau</persName>’s recent
                    telegram to the President<note n="5" xml:id="d324fn5">See telegram from the
                        Commission to Negotiate Peace no. 3251, July 21, 9 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_288">p. 288</ref>.</note> as to whether this Government is
                    disposed to furnish the needed number of troops to replace Czecho-Slovaks when
                    the latter are withdrawn from Siberia please say that, with the utmost regret,
                    the President finds it impracticable to furnish additional American troops for
                    this purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
